author: mrrgolfballing
description: Kim Jong-il‚Äôs official biography claims that in his first and only round of golf, he shot 38 under par, including 11 holes-in-one. This incredible feat was reported by North Korean state media and took place on a Pyongyang golf course in 1994. While the story is widely known, golf authorities have expressed skepticism about the accuracy of such a low score, especially the 11 holes-in-one. The theory how that stat had entered into the official record was: The scorekeeper tracking Kim‚Äôs round that day had relied on a relative-to-par system, marking down 0 for pars, 1 for bogeys and 2 for double-bogeys. Unfamiliar with that scorekeeping shorthand, the North Korean state news agency covering the outing had read the 1s on Kim‚Äôs card as holes-in-one. Follow me for more!
